race.comment: ZENTORNO (4) jumped out well and was much too good for the Mildura Maidens first-up, winning by 3L. He was backed off the map and impressed. Presents fitter will be suited stepping up to a mile. He can take the next step for a smart stable. SHAL EXCEED (1) was safely held over 1700m at Warrnambool but belted home from the back winning this grade at Mildura prior. Finally draws an inside gate and he can bounce back. OLIVIA'S SCANDAL (6) finished 1.3 lengths behind the winner over 1400m at Echuca after lifting strongly to win at Gunbower. John Allen is a key jockey engagement and a bounce is also on the cards. CHOSEN VENTURE (2) comes off Opens at the picnics on a 3 day return. He's won 4/9 at the track and jumps from a low gate. Must be pleasing.
